World Food Prize Awarded to Ex-Presidents of Ghana, Brazil

-- B y   A l a n   B j e r g a
-- 
2011-06-21T17:20:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/world-food-prize-awarded-to-former-presidents-of-ghana-brazil.html
Former presidents John Kufuor of
 Ghana  and  Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva  of  Brazil  are the 2011
winners of the  World Food Prize , awarded annually for efforts to
alleviate global hunger and poverty through agriculture.  Kufuor and Lula de Silva, who will share a $250,000 cash
award, will be honored in October at a conference in Des Moines,
Iowa. The winners were announced today in  Washington .  Prize officials said Kufuor was honored for leading efforts
that resulted in the percentage of hungry in Ghana falling to 9
percent in 2004 from 34 percent in 1990. Lula received the award
for helping to reduce the level of extreme poverty in his
country to 4.8 percent in 2009 from 12 percent in 2003.  Sponsors  include the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, the
John Deere Foundation,  Monsanto Co. (MON) , DuPont Co., Archer Daniels
Midland Co., PepsiCo Inc., General Mills Co. and Cargill Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Bjerga in Washington at 
 abjerga@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net . 